{"info": {"author": "Charles Hessel", "author_email": "charles.hessel@ens-paris-saclay.fr", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# Ponomarenko: noise curve estimation from a single image\n\nPython bindings for Miguel Colom's implementation of the Ponomarenko et al.\nmethod.\n\nVersion 0.0.4 -- March 23, 2020\n\nBy Charles Hessel <charles.hessel@ens-paris-saclay.fr>\n\nThe C++ code used in this repository has been peer-reviewed as part of the IPOL\npublication:\n> Miguel Colom, and Antoni Buades, Analysis and Extension of the Ponomarenko et\n  al. Method, Estimating a Noise Curve from a Single Image, Image Processing On\n  Line, 3 (2013), pp. 173\u2013197. https://doi.org/10.5201/ipol.2013.45\n\n\n## Installation\n\nRun\n```\npip install -e .\n```\nfrom the directory where `setup.py` is located.\n\n\n## Usage\n\n\n### As a Python module\n\n```python\nfrom ponomarenko import estimate_noise\n\nbins, noise_std = estimate_noise(image)\n```\n\nThe method estimates the standard-deviation of the noise (in `noise_std`) in\ndifferent intensity bins, which centers are given in the first output `bins`.", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/cmla/ponomarenko.git", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "ponomarenko", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/ponomarenko/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/ponomarenko/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/cmla/ponomarenko.git"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/ponomarenko/0.0.4.post1/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=3.5", "summary": "Python bindings for M. Colom's IPOL Ponomarenko implementation", "version": "0.0.4.post1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Ponomarenko: noise curve estimation from a single image</h1>\n<p>Python bindings for Miguel Colom's implementation of the Ponomarenko et al.\nmethod.</p>\n<p>Version 0.0.4 -- March 23, 2020</p>\n<p>By Charles Hessel <a href=\"mailto:charles.hessel@ens-paris-saclay.fr\">charles.hessel@ens-paris-saclay.fr</a></p>\n<p>The C++ code used in this repository has been peer-reviewed as part of the IPOL\npublication:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Miguel Colom, and Antoni Buades, Analysis and Extension of the Ponomarenko et\nal. Method, Estimating a Noise Curve from a Single Image, Image Processing On\nLine, 3 (2013), pp. 173\u2013197. <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.5201/ipol.2013.45\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://doi.org/10.5201/ipol.2013.45</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Run</p>\n<pre><code>pip install -e .\n</code></pre>\n<p>from the directory where <code>setup.py</code> is located.</p>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<h3>As a Python module</h3>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">ponomarenko</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">estimate_noise</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">bins</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">noise_std</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">estimate_noise</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">image</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<p>The method estimates the standard-deviation of the noise (in <code>noise_std</code>) in\ndifferent intensity bins, which centers are given in the first output <code>bins</code>.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6867349, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "7a6ed926f3110db98a5495e16a773c04", "sha256": "470a7464300a8301681acfa43cce2c0f62405e8808558297aefcf57e9a667ced"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "ponomarenko-0.0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "7a6ed926f3110db98a5495e16a773c04", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.5", "size": 3356, "upload_time": "2020-03-20T20:59:46", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-20T20:59:46.1